@startuml dspace-group_simphera-reference-architecture-azure

actor "DevOps Engineer" as DevOps
participant "Terraform" as TF
participant "Azure Resource Manager" as ARM
participant "Azure Kubernetes Service" as AKS
participant "Azure Database for PostgreSQL" as PostgreSQL
participant "Azure Storage Account" as Storage
participant "Azure Key Vault" as KeyVault
participant "Azure Virtual Network" as VNet
participant "Azure Private Link" as PrivateLink
participant "Azure Log Analytics" as LogAnalytics
participant "Azure Bastion" as Bastion

DevOps -> TF: Apply Terraform configuration
activate TF

TF -> ARM: Create resource group
activate ARM

TF -> VNet: Create virtual network and subnets
activate VNet

TF -> KeyVault: Create Key Vault
activate KeyVault

TF -> AKS: Provision Kubernetes cluster
activate AKS

TF -> PostgreSQL: Create PostgreSQL flexible servers
activate PostgreSQL

TF -> Storage: Create Storage Accounts for MinIO
activate Storage

TF -> PrivateLink: Configure Private Link for PaaS services
activate PrivateLink

TF -> LogAnalytics: Set up Log Analytics workspace (optional)
activate LogAnalytics

TF -> Bastion: Provision Bastion host (optional)
activate Bastion

ARM --> TF: Resources created
TF --> DevOps: Deployment complete

TF -> TF: Output resource information

DevOps -> AKS: Access Kubernetes cluster
AKS --> DevOps: Provide kubeconfig

DevOps -> PostgreSQL: Connect to databases
PostgreSQL --> DevOps: Provide connection strings

DevOps -> Storage: Access MinIO storage
Storage --> DevOps: Provide access keys

DevOps -> KeyVault: Retrieve secrets
KeyVault --> DevOps: Provide secure access to secrets

DevOps -> Bastion: Connect to VMs (if needed)
Bastion --> DevOps: Provide secure access to VMs

deactivate TF
deactivate ARM
deactivate VNet
deactivate KeyVault
deactivate AKS
deactivate PostgreSQL
deactivate Storage
deactivate PrivateLink
deactivate LogAnalytics
deactivate Bastion

@enduml